There are two ways to achieve this. One using JavaScript and the other using CSS

**Using CSS: (Recommended Way)**&lt;br&gt;
Css has a property called `text-overflow: ellipsis;` this property cuts off the text for **fixed-width** html elements and adds `...` at the end. Make sure to set `max-width` and `overflow: hidden`

See in the snippet below:

&lt;!-- begin snippet: js hide: false console: true babel: false --&gt;

&lt;!-- language: lang-css --&gt;

    .text-overflow-test td {
      max-width: 200px;
      overflow: hidden;
      text-overflow: ellipsis;
      white-space: nowrap;
    }

&lt;!-- language: lang-html --&gt;

    &lt;table class=&quot;text-overflow-test&quot; border=&quot;1&quot;&gt;
      &lt;tbody&gt;
        &lt;tr&gt;
          &lt;td&gt;This is short text&lt;/td&gt;
          &lt;td&gt;This is short text&lt;/td&gt;
        &lt;/tr&gt;
        &lt;tr&gt;
          &lt;td&gt;This is very long long long very long long long very long long long text&lt;/td&gt;
          &lt;td&gt;This is very long long long very long long long very long long long text&lt;/td&gt;
        &lt;/tr&gt;
      &lt;/tbody&gt;
    &lt;/table&gt;

&lt;!-- end snippet --&gt;

**Using Javascript:**&lt;br&gt;
Check if length is greater then 15. Slice the text and add ... at the end.

&lt;!-- begin snippet: js hide: false console: true babel: false --&gt;

&lt;!-- language: lang-js --&gt;

    const data = [
    	{text: &quot;less than 15&quot;},
    	{text: &quot;This text is a lot more than just 15 characters&quot;},
    	{text: &quot;15   characters&quot;},
    ]

    const slicer = (text) =&gt; text.length &gt; 15 ? text.slice(0,15) + &#39;...&#39; : text

    const slicedData = data.map(obj =&gt; {
    	return {
    		text: slicer(obj.text)
    	}
    })

    console.log(slicedData)

&lt;!-- end snippet --&gt;

The javascript way is not recommended as it alters the actual data that you are passing to the table resulting in loss of information.

You can use css property `text-overflow` for this case.

&lt;!-- begin snippet: js hide: false console: true babel: false --&gt;

&lt;!-- language: lang-css --&gt;

    .long-cell {
      max-width: 100px;
      overflow: hidden;
      text-overflow: ellipsis;
      white-space: nowrap;
    }

&lt;!-- language: lang-html --&gt;

    &lt;table&gt;
    &lt;thead&gt;
      &lt;th&gt;Col 1&lt;/th&gt;
      &lt;th&gt;Col 2&lt;/th&gt;
